  "id": "BIT-nginx-gateway-2026-42946",
  "summary": "NGINX ngx_http_scgi_module and ngx_http_uwsgi_module vulnerability",
  "details": "A vulnerability exists in the ngx_http_scgi_module and ngx_http_uwsgi_module modules that may result in excessive memory allocation or an over-read of data. When scgi_pass or uwsgi_pass is configured, an unauthenticated attacker with man-in-the-middle (MITM) ability to control responses from an upstream server may be able to read the memory of the NGINX worker process or restart it.  Note: Software versions which have reached End of Technical Support (EoTS) are not evaluated.",
